        public static void write(java.lang.String path,
                         org.jarpm.config.structs.Config configData)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        Writes configuration data to a config file. If the file is nonexistent, it creates the file. path must not point nonexistent directories, as it will throw an IOException.
        Parameters:
        path - The path to create the configuration file at
        configData - The configuration data to write
